		<li id="comment-1267">
			<div class="comment"><span class="commentauthor"><span style=""><a href='http://admin' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Tim</a></span> says:</span>
						<br />

			<small><a href="#comments-1267" title="">April 23rd, 2009 at 8:47 am</a> </small></div>

			<div class="comment"><div style="font-weight: bold;">
<p>Aparna: I am SO glad you liked it. Salt is used in desserts to enhance flavors. It is actually quite important in very sweet things like the caramel glaze- it helps keep things balanced. I usually even increase the amount of salt dessert recipes call for because I think it is such an important addition. You can experiment though and see what you think of the glaze without the salt, whatever tastes best to you is right!</p>
</div>
</div>

