<p>I used AP Flour (scant 2C), honey instead of corn syrup, and I didn&#8217;t have a candy thermometer so I boiled the caramel mixture for about 13 minutes. Next time I will boil for a few minutes less as I think a thinner sauce would coat the cake better. I was so antsy that I even forgot to add in the vanilla (!). So, I pretty much butchered your recipe but It was still delish! Thank you!</p>
